message.content:
Bill Clinton was the President of the United States in 1996. He served as the 42nd president from January 20, 1993, to January 20, 2001. His vice president during this time was Al Gore. Clinton's presidency is notable for a strong economy, an impeachment trial in the Senate, and his administration's efforts to reform healthcare through the unsuccessful Hillarycare plan.

If you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
